    },
    "subtype": "weapon",
    "text": "The adze\u2019s smaller version is useful for delicate woodworking in cramped spaces. Tripkees use hand adzes for crafting and as close quarters weapons.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 170,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "52e96f4918ed43308370f4576b59947c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Agile",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "The multiple attack penalty you take with this weapon on the second attack on your turn is \u20134 instead of \u20135, and \u20138 instead of \u201310 on the third and subsequent attacks in the turn.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 179,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "6a57956799f3d30121d529e48f12904c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Finesse",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "You can use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls using this melee weapon. You still calculate damage using Strength.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 194,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "435cbfa8d6a3da2e6b53b01082b49f7d",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Sweep",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 283,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This weapon makes wide swinging attacks. When you attack with this weapon, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your attack roll if you already attempted to attack a different target this turn using this weapon.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 195,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "c42503980965022311443a6e1e55ab57",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Thrown",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 283",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 283,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "You can throw this weapon as a ranged attack; it is a ranged weapon when thrown. You add your Strength modifier to damage as you would for a melee weapon. When this trait appears on a melee weapon, it also includes the range increment. Ranged weapons with this trait use the range increment in the weapon\u2019s Range entry.",
        "type": "trait",
        "value": "10 ft."
      },
